-- Bank of America shares up on Lewis retirement
-- 
-- Wed Sep 30, 2009 5:54pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/09/30/us-markets-stocks-afterthebell-bofa-sb-idUSTRE58T7AE20090930

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Bank of America rose 1.4 percent after the closing bell on Wednesday after it announced the retirement of Chief Executive Ken Lewis. 

 Shares were up at $17.16 after closing on the New York Stock Exchange at $16.92.